# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   See https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/COMMANDS.md#pyenv-version-file
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used in a vitualenv, the virtualenv directory itself should be ignored.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#.pdm-python
#.pdm-build/

# pipxml
